  "summary": "This chunk details conjurations and ritual procedures from the Munich Handbook (CLM 849), focusing on image magic for Friday (Venus) and Saturday (Saturn). It includes lists of angels, winds, planetary rulers, and temporal hierarchies tied to months, days, hours, and cardinal directions. The Saturn section describes binding rituals involving images made of pitch, with specific incantations invoking spirits like Castuel, Matraton, Satael, and Amamnim. Temporal frameworks include 12 monthly princes (e.g., Ragiel, Dyrnaot), four seasonal divisions each governed by three angels, and daily/hourly angelic rulers (e.g., Raphael for Sunday/first hour). Protective circles, ritual tools (gladius), and ingredients (cera alba, pice clara) are also specified.",
  "key_passages": [
    "[...] hanc autem ymaginem mandant isti angeli: Castuel, Maratron uel Matraton, Satael. Et venti huic seruientes sunt hij: Memmi, Aloybain, Aflas, Analuabith.",
